dc_title_s: Diocese de Rheins et le pais de Rethelpar Jean Jubrien
dc_description_s: 1 map ; 39 x 50 cm|Relief shown pictorially.|Decorative title cartouche depicting cupids and a monster face. The scale cartouche depicting dividers and his tools. In the upper right corner of the map two cherubs hold a banner depicting the Reims coat of arms and Rethel coat of arms.|This state was published in atlases by Jan Jansson in 1636, 1637, and 1680.|From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan.
